            "url": {
              "raw": "{{url}}/auth/register",
              "host": [
                "{{url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Registers a new user account.\n\n## Purpose\n\nCreate a new user in the system using basic profile details and a password. This endpoint is typically the first step before logging in.\n\n## Method & URL\n\n`POST {{url}}/auth/register`\n\n## Authentication\n\nNone (public endpoint).\n\n## Headers\n\n| Header | Value | Notes |  \n| --- | --- | --- | --- |  \n| `Accept` | `application/json` | Requests JSON responses |\n\n> If your API requires JSON request parsing, ensure you send `Content-Type: application/json` (some backends infer it automatically, but it’s commonly required). \n  \n\n## Request Body (JSON)\n\nSend a JSON object with the following fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Constraints / Notes |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `first_name` | string | Yes | Non-empty; typically 2–50 chars |\n| `last_name` | string | Yes | Non-empty; typically 2–50 chars |\n| `email` | string | Yes | Must be a valid email format; must be unique |\n| `password` | string | Yes | Minimum length enforced by backend (commonly 8+); avoid weak passwords |\n| `password_confirmation` | string | Yes | Must match `password` |\n| `date_of_birth` | string | Yes | Date string in `YYYY-MM-DD` format |\n\n### Example request payload\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"first_name\": \"hamza\",\n  \"last_name\": \"hajjaji\",\n  \"email\": \"hajjaji@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password\",\n  \"password_confirmation\": \"password\",\n  \"date_of_birth\": \"2004-06-12\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n## Expected Responses\n\n### `201 Created`\n\nUser registered successfully.\n\nExample shape:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"message\": \"Registered successfully\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"id\": 123,\n    \"first_name\": \"hamza\",\n    \"last_name\": \"hajjaji\",\n    \"email\": \"hajjaji@gmail.com\",\n    \"date_of_birth\": \"2004-06-12\",\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-03-16T12:34:56Z\"\n  }\n}\n\n ```\n\n### `422 Unprocessable Entity`\n\nValidation failed (missing/invalid fields).\n\nExample shape:\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"message\": \"The given data was invalid.\",\n  \"errors\": {\n    \"email\": [\"The email field must be a valid email address.\"],\n    \"password\": [\"The password field must be at least 8 characters.\"],\n    \"password_confirmation\": [\"The password confirmation does not match.\"]\n  }\n}\n\n ```"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "let jsonData = pm.response.json();\r",
                  "\r",
                  "let token = null;\r",
                  "\r",
                  "if (jsonData.token) {\r",
                  "    token = jsonData.token;\r",
                  "}\r",
                  "\r",
                  "if(token) {\r",
                  "    pm.environment.set(\"token\", token);\r",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\r\n    \"email\": \"hamza@gmail.com\",\r\n    \"password\": \"password\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{url}}/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{url}}"
