            "description": "### Login\nAuthenticates a user with email + password and returns an access token (when credentials are valid).\n\n**Method:** `POST`  \n**URL:** `{{url}}/auth/login`\n\n---\n\n### Required headers\n| Header | Value | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Accept` | `application/json` | Indicates the client expects a JSON response. |\n\n---\n\n### Request body (JSON)\n**Schema**\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"string\",\n  \"password\": \"string\"\n}\n```\n\n**Example**\n```json\n{\n  \"email\": \"hamza@gmail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Responses\n#### 200 OK (success)\nReturns a JSON response that includes a `token` field.\n\nExample shape:\n```json\n{\n  \"token\": \"<jwt-or-access-token>\"\n}\n```\n\n#### 401 Unauthorized (error)\nReturned when credentials are invalid or the user is not authorized.\n\nExample:\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"Unauthorized\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Postman behavior\nThis request has an existing post-response script that checks the response JSON for `token` and, when present, saves it into the active environment variable **`token`** (i.e., `pm.environment.set('token', token)`).\n"
          },
          "response": []
        },
