              ],
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "refresh"
              ]
            },
            "description": "### Refresh Token\n\nRefreshes the current authentication token by calling the refresh endpoint.\n\n#### Endpoint\n\n`POST {{url}}/auth/refresh`\n\n#### Required variables\n\n- `{{url}}` — Base API URL (set in the active environment **al-madar-bank**).\n- `token` — Current access token stored as an environment variable.\n\n> Note: This request expects the token to be sent according to your API’s auth mechanism (for example, `Authorization: Bearer {{token}}` if configured at a parent folder/collection). This request itself is currently documented without changing its headers/auth settings.\n\n#### Expected response\n\nA JSON object containing a refreshed token.\n\nTypical shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"token\": \"<new_access_token>\"\n}\n```\n\n#### Post-response behavior\n\nThis request includes a post-response script that:\n\n1. Parses the JSON response (`pm.response.json()`)\n2. Reads `jsonData.token`\n3. If present, saves it into the active environment:\n\n```javascript\npm.environment.set(\"token\", token);\n```\n\nThis updates the `token` environment variable for subsequent requests.\n\n---\n\n### Examples\n\n**Example request**\n\n```http\nPOST {{url}}/auth/refresh\nAccept: application/json\n```\n\n**Example response**\n\n```http\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  \"token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\"\n}\n```"
          },
          "response": []
