            "description": "Retrieves the profile of the currently authenticated user.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n`GET {{url}}/users/me`\n\n### Base URL\n\nThis request uses the environment variable `{{url}}` as the API base URL (for example: `https://api.your-domain.com`).\n\n### Authentication\n\nRequires a Bearer access token stored in the environment variable `{{token}}`.\n\nSend the token as:\n\n``` http\nAuthorization: Bearer {{token}}\n\n ```\n\n### Headers\n\n``` http\nAccept: application/json\n\n ```\n\n### Success response (200)\n\nReturns a `data` object containing the authenticated user.\n\nCommon fields:\n\n- `data.id` (number) — User ID\n    \n- `data.first_name` (string)\n    \n- `data.last_name` (string)\n    \n- `data.email` (string)\n    \n- `data.date_of_birth` (string, `YYYY-MM-DD`)\n    \n- `data.created_at` (string/datetime)\n    \n- `data.updated_at` (string/datetime)\n    \n\n### Common error codes\n\n- **401 Unauthorized** — Missing/invalid/expired token\n    \n- **403 Forbidden** — Authenticated but not allowed to access this resource\n    \n- **404 Not Found** — Route/resource not found\n    \n- **422 Unprocessable Entity** — Validation error (if applicable)\n    \n- **500 Internal Server Error** — Unexpected server error"
          },
          "response": []
